Title: Approximate Bertrand Equilibria in a Replicated Industry
Abstract: This paper considers the existence and properties of approximate Bertrand equilibria in a replicated industry. Price setting firms produce a homogeneous product with weakly convex costs. The main results are that: (a) Given ɛ &gt; 0, an ɛ-equilibrium exists if the industry is large enough; (b) If the ɛ is small enough, and the industry large enough, any ɛ-equilibrium is approximately competitive. These results depend on how contingent demand is specified.
